Single Middle-aged male: (Mark, age 45)

Mark is a project manager at a furniture manufacturing company who works full-time and manages multiple responsibilities. 
He earns a stable salary but feels like he doesn’t always have a clear picture of where his money goes each month. 
Between mortgage payments, utilities, groceries, insurance, subscriptions, and occasional travel, his expenses add up quickly. 
He currently uses a basic spreadsheet but finds it time-consuming and difficult to visualize trends.

Mark is comfortable with business software and data dashboards, but he does not want to manually build a complex dashboard
and would prefer to have as little input as possible for initial setup, without compromising security. 

Mark user stories:
As a user with numerous expenses, I want the software to be clean and free of clutter, ensuring he can check in on his finances during his busy workday
As a user with many responsibilities, I want the setup process to be straighforward.

As a user with an existing spreadsheet, I want to be able to import what I already have so I don't need to start from scratch.

Requirement Specification:
The system shall allow Mark to automatically track and categorize all his monthly expenses, providing a clear overview of where his money is going without requiring extensive manual input. 
It shall generate simple, uncluttered visual summaries and highlight spending trends to help him quickly understand his financial situation. 
The app shall ensure security while minimizing setup effort and allow easy access during his busy workday.
